# Tests for the rental agreement formalization

These test scopes pin the expected outputs of the model with `assertion`s, so
`catala interpret` (or `catala test-scope`) fails loudly on any regression.

> Using Rental_agreement

## §5 Late fee — boundary cases

Day 1: inside the 3-day grace period → no fee.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestLateFeeDay1:
  output late_fee content money
  fee scope Rental_agreement.LateFeeCalculation
scope TestLateFeeDay1:
  definition fee.payment_day equals 1
  definition late_fee equals fee.late_fee
  assertion late_fee = $0.00
```

Day 3: last day of the grace period → still no fee.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestLateFeeDay3:
  output late_fee content money
  fee scope Rental_agreement.LateFeeCalculation
scope TestLateFeeDay3:
  definition fee.payment_day equals 3
  definition late_fee equals fee.late_fee
  assertion late_fee = $0.00
```

Day 4: first late day → flat $25, no per-day surcharge yet.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestLateFeeDay4:
  output late_fee content money
  fee scope Rental_agreement.LateFeeCalculation
scope TestLateFeeDay4:
  definition fee.payment_day equals 4
  definition late_fee equals fee.late_fee
  assertion late_fee = $25.00
```

Day 6: $25 flat + 2 days × $5 = $35.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestLateFeeDay6:
  output late_fee content money
  fee scope Rental_agreement.LateFeeCalculation
scope TestLateFeeDay6:
  definition fee.payment_day equals 6
  definition late_fee equals fee.late_fee
  assertion late_fee = $35.00
```

Day 10: $25 flat + 6 days × $5 = $55.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestLateFeeDay10:
  output late_fee content money
  fee scope Rental_agreement.LateFeeCalculation
scope TestLateFeeDay10:
  definition fee.payment_day equals 10
  definition late_fee equals fee.late_fee
  assertion late_fee = $55.00
```

## §2 + §5 Monthly total due

Paid on time (day 2): just the base rent.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestTotalOnTime:
  output total_due content money
  stmt scope Rental_agreement.MonthlyRentStatement
scope TestTotalOnTime:
  definition stmt.payment_day equals 2
  definition total_due equals stmt.total_due
  assertion total_due = $685.00
```

Paid late (day 4): rent $685 + late fee $25 = $710.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestTotalLate:
  output total_due content money
  stmt scope Rental_agreement.MonthlyRentStatement
scope TestTotalLate:
  definition stmt.payment_day equals 4
  definition total_due equals stmt.total_due
  assertion total_due = $710.00
```

## §7 + §8 Security deposit refund

Clean, no damage → full $685 refunded.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestRefundClean:
  output refund content money
  r scope Rental_agreement.SecurityDepositRefund
scope TestRefundClean:
  definition r.damages equals $0.00
  definition r.returned_clean equals true
  definition refund equals r.refund
  assertion refund = $685.00
```

Not clean, $100 damage → $685 − $200 − $100 = $385.

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestRefundDirtyWithDamage:
  output refund content money
  r scope Rental_agreement.SecurityDepositRefund
scope TestRefundDirtyWithDamage:
  definition r.damages equals $100.00
  definition r.returned_clean equals false
  definition refund equals r.refund
  assertion refund = $385.00
```

Damage exceeds the deposit → refund floored at $0 (never negative).

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestRefundFloored:
  output refund content money
  r scope Rental_agreement.SecurityDepositRefund
scope TestRefundFloored:
  definition r.damages equals $1,000.00
  definition r.returned_clean equals false
  definition refund equals r.refund
  assertion refund = $0.00
```
